## Example 2: Multiple Algorithm Calls (Composite Algorithm)

```csharp
private void button15_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    // When an algorithm makes multiple internal calls (as seen here with 8 RunMidpointCircle calls),
    // we measure the ENTIRE operation as a single unit. This gives us the total time
    // and resource cost of the composite drawing operation.
    
    BeginPerformanceMeasurement("CompositeCircles");
    ClearCanvas();
    
    int xc = pictureBox1.Width / 2;
    int yc = pictureBox1.Height / 2;

    // All of these RunMidpointCircle calls happen between Begin and End measurement
    // They execute in the same mode (both detect IsSlow("CompositeCircles"))
    RunMidpointCircle(xc, yc, 120, Color.Black, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc - 50, yc - 30, 25, Color.Blue, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc - 50, yc - 30, 7, Color.Black, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc + 50, yc - 30, 25, Color.Blue, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc + 50, yc - 30, 7, Color.Black, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc - 100, yc - 90, 45, Color.Gray, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc + 100, yc - 90, 45, Color.Gray, bmp);
    RunMidpointCircle(xc, yc + 60, 30, Color.Red, bmp);

    pictureBox1.Image = bmp;
    
    // The measurement captures the TOTAL time for drawing all 8 circles
    // Result might show: "CompositeCircles: 45.23ms SLOW"
    EndPerformanceMeasurement();
}
```

**Key Points:**
- Multiple algorithm calls within a single measurement = combined metrics
- Useful for understanding total performance of complex operations
- Shows educational value: How long does it take to render everything?

