## Example 6: How the Display Label Updates

After `EndPerformanceMeasurement()`, this method is automatically called:

```csharp
private void UpdatePerformanceDisplay(string algorithmName, PerformanceSnapshot snapshot)
{
    // Thread-safe invoke (ensures UI updates only on UI thread)
    if (InvokeRequired)
    {
        Invoke(new Action(() => UpdatePerformanceDisplay(algorithmName, snapshot)));
        return;
    }

    // Build display text with latest metrics and comparison
    string displayText = "PERFORMANCE METRICS\n";
    displayText += "???????????????????????????????????\n\n";

    displayText += $"Algorithm: {algorithmName}\n";
    displayText += $"Mode: {(snapshot.IsSlowMode ? "SLOW (Animated)" : "FAST (Direct)")}\n\n";

    displayText += "Last Execution:\n";
    displayText += $"  Time:   {snapshot.ExecutionTimeMs:F2} ms\n";
    displayText += $"  CPU:    {snapshot.CpuPercent:F1} %\n";
    displayText += $"  Memory: {snapshot.MemoryMB:F3} MB\n\n";

    // Try to get comparison between slow and fast modes
    string comparison = PerformanceMonitor.GetPerformanceComparison(algorithmName);
    if (!comparison.Contains("Insufficient"))
    {
        displayText += "SLOW vs FAST Comparison:\n";
        displayText += comparison + "\n";
    }

    displayText += "\n[Double-click to copy]";

    lblPerformanceMetrics.Text = displayText;
}
```

