## Memory Architecture

```
PerformanceMonitor._metricsHistory Dictionary:
{
  "DDA": [
    PerformanceSnapshot { 
      ExecutionTimeMs: 8.76, 
      CpuPercent: 5.3, 
      IsSlowMode: false,
      AlgorithmName: "DDA",
      CapturedAt: 2024-01-15 14:32:45
    },
    PerformanceSnapshot { 
      ExecutionTimeMs: 125.43, 
      CpuPercent: 15.2, 
      IsSlowMode: true,
      AlgorithmName: "DDA",
      CapturedAt: 2024-01-15 14:32:50
    },
    ... more snapshots ...
  ],
  "Bresenham": [
    PerformanceSnapshot { ... },
    ... snapshots ...
  ],
  ... other algorithms ...
}

When GetPerformanceComparison("DDA") is called:
1. Retrieves all DDA snapshots from dictionary
2. Partitions into:
   - SLOW list: [125.43ms, 128.12ms, ...]
   - FAST list: [8.76ms, 8.93ms, ...]
3. Computes:
   - slowAvg = (125.43 + 128.12 + ...) / count
   - fastAvg = (8.76 + 8.93 + ...) / count
   - ratio = slowAvg / fastAvg
4. Returns formatted string with comparison
```

